com.github.xemiru.luamesh

Annotation Type LuaType


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value={TYPE,METHOD})
public @interface LuaType
    Defines class and class members able to be pushed into a Lua environment.

    Target classes and/or members must be public.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      boolean abstractt
      Marks this member as abstract.
      LuaType.MetaEntry entry
      Sets where the member is placed in the object's metatable entry.
      java.lang.String name
      Overrides the name of this object when its passed into a Lua object's metatable.

    • Element Detail

      • name

        public abstract java.lang.String name
        Overrides the name of this object when its passed into a Lua object's metatable.

        Names are completely ignored if this member is not placed in LuaType.MetaEntry.INDEX.

        Returns:
        the override for the target member's Lua name, or empty string if no override
        Default:
        ""

      • abstractt

        public abstract boolean abstractt
        Marks this member as abstract. Applies to methods only.

        If the method is marked abstract, the method body is ignored and the Lua object holding the abstract method is required to implement the corresponding function, checked upon calling the method.

        Returns:
        if the method is marked as "empty"
        Default:
        false

      • entry

        public abstract LuaType.MetaEntry entry
        Sets where the member is placed in the object's metatable entry. This is ignored when the target element is a class/type.

        By default, members are placed in LuaType.MetaEntry.INDEX.

        Returns:
        the MetaEntry to place the target member in
        Default:
        com.github.xemiru.luamesh.LuaType.MetaEntry.INDEX
